TITLE: Creating an Excalibur Engine Instance
DESCRIPTION: Initializes the Excalibur game engine with a specified width and height. The engine is the main container that manages the game loop, scenes, and rendering.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excaliburjs/Excalibur/blob/main/site/docs/00-tutorial/00-breakout.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_1

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
// Create an instance of the engine.
// I'm specifying that the game be 800 pixels wide by 600 pixels tall.
// If no dimensions are specified the game will fit to the screen.
const game = new Engine({
  width: 800,
  height: 600,
});
```

