TITLE: Creating and Starting an Excalibur Game Instance
DESCRIPTION: Demonstrates how to create a new Excalibur game instance with configuration options and start the game. It shows setting up the canvas size, display mode, and pointer scope.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excaliburjs/Excalibur/blob/main/site/docs/02-fundamentals/04-architecture.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_0

LANGUAGE: typescript
CODE:
```
const game = new ex.Engine({
  width: 800, // the width of the canvas
  height: 600, // the height of the canvas
  canvasElementId: '', // the DOM canvas element ID, if you are providing your own
  displayMode: ex.DisplayMode.FitScreen, // the display mode
  pointerScope: ex.PointerScope.Document // the scope of capturing pointer (mouse/touch) events
});
// call game.start, which is a Promise
game.start().then(function () {
  // ready, set, go!
});
```

