TITLE: Creating Tilemap Bitmasks in TypeScript with Excalibur.js
DESCRIPTION: This function loops through each tile in a tilemap and assigns a bitmask value based on the state of neighboring tiles. It creates an array of bitmask values that correspond to each tile in the map, which will later be used to determine which tile sprite to display.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excaliburjs/Excalibur/blob/main/site/blog/2024-07-02-autotiling/AT.mdx#2025-04-16_snippet_3

