TITLE: Creating a StrictEventEmitter with Type Checking in Excalibur
DESCRIPTION: This snippet shows how to create a StrictEventEmitter class that enforces compile-time checking of event names. It demonstrates the implementation with a Player class that has a health system, showing how TypeScript catches typos in event names during development.
