TITLE: Pixel Art Filtering Shader (GLSL)
DESCRIPTION: The GLSL shader code used by Excalibur to implement high-quality pixel art filtering. This Inigo Quilez pixel art filter adjusts UVs and applies subtle subpixel antialiasing to eliminate common pixel art artifacts.
SOURCE: https://github.com/excaliburjs/Excalibur/blob/main/site/blog/2025-03-10-new-year/2025-03-10-new-year.md#2025-04-16_snippet_7

LANGUAGE: c
CODE:
```
// Inigo Quilez pixel art filter 
// https://jorenjoestar.github.io/post/pixel_art_filtering/
vec2 uv_iq(in vec2 uv, in vec2 texture_size) {
  vec2 pixel = uv * texture_size;

  vec2 seam=floor(pixel+.5);
  vec2 dudv=fwidth(pixel);
  pixel=seam+clamp((pixel-seam)/dudv,-.5,.5);

  return pixel/texture_size;
}
```

